===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# {{lb|zh|archaic|of feudal lords or high officials}} to [[pass away]]; to [[die]]
#: {{zh-x|會 ^延平王 ^成功 薨，長{zhǎng}子 ^經 嗣立，^臺灣 初 稱 ^東都{dū}，改 ^明京 以 候 ^桂王 之 蹕。|When {{w|Koxinga}} (''Zheng Chenggong'') '''passed away''', his eldest son ''{{w|Zheng Jing|Jing}}'' succeeded to the throne. Taiwan was initially named ''Dongdu'' [The Eastern Capital], then changed to ''Mingjing'' [Capital of the {{w|Ming Dynasty}}] to await the arrival of the {{w|Zhu Youlang|Prince of Gui}}.|CL|ref={{lw|zh|查繼佐}}, {{lang|zh|《東山國語》}}, [[s:zh:東山國語/臺灣前語|臺灣前語]]}} {{attention|zh|please check}}
# {{lb|zh|onomatopoeia}} [[swarming]]; [[flocking]]; [[noisy]]
#: {{zh-x|螽斯 羽，薨-薨 兮！宜 爾 子孫，繩-繩 兮！|Grasshoppers on the wing — <br>Your racket goes <i>'''hmoong-hmoong'''</i>!<br>No wonder your children — <br>They are all like, ''bleng-bleng''!|CL|ref={{circa2|11th century {{BC}} — 7th century {{BC}}}}, The ''[[w:Classic of Poetry|Classic of Poetry]]''. The translation here emphasises the onomatopoeic nature of the ideophonic reduplications.}}

